<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="680" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d680">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">600.119/1899: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-24">December 24,
                                1918</date>.<lb/>[Received December 24—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>4839. War Trade Board [from Sheldon]: Number 2160. Supplementing our 2067
                        December 12. Proclamation about to be issued makes trade resumption
                        effective January 1st with (1) Alsace-Lorraine and with (2) the new Italian
                        territories included in line defined by Austrian, Italian armistice of
                        November 3d.<note n="45" xml:id="d680fn45">For text, see <ref target="#pg_175">p. 175</ref>.</note> Specific reference to Trieste
                        and Trentino will not be made.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>